        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 2:11PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 211 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Old Station, or 24 miles northeast of Mineral, moving west at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crater Lake Campground and Ca 44 At Shasta-Lassen Co Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
